      "blocks": {
        "rich_text_mJCVmN": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "1st para",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>When it comes to fine jewelry that can truly keep up with modern life, few designs offer the security, durability, and <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/sports-collection\" title=\"On the move jewelry\">daily wearability</a> of the Bezel Setting. Unlike traditional prong settings that leave diamonds exposed, Bezel Settings fully encase each stone in a protective setting of gold offering unmatched strength, smooth wear, and long-term peace of mind.</p><p>In this guide, we’ll break down the full anatomy of a Bezel Setting from its unique components and setting styles to why it’s the perfect choice for active lifestyles, sports, and jewelry that’s truly made to move with you.</p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_mmd6EJ": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>The Bezel Setting: What It Really Means</h2>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_M3ectN": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "name": "The Bezel Setting: What It Really Means",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/The_Anatomy_of_a_Bezel_Setting_Components_Types_Durability_355_x_355_px_Inside_1st_Image.png",
            "text": "<p>At its core, a Bezel Setting is pretty straightforward: it wraps a band of metal around the edges of a gemstone, securing it in place. This metal rim can either fully enclose the stone or leave parts of it exposed, depending on the design.</p><p>But behind that simplicity lies a lot of intentional design. A well-made Bezel Setting doesn’t just hold the diamond, it frames it. It enhances the stone’s shape, controls how much light enters, and protects against chips or snags. It’s a form that meets function in a way that feels timeless.</p>",
            "layout_direction": "row",
            "reverse_layout": false,
            "custom_id": "what-it-means",
            "image_size_option": "adaptive",
            "show_products": true,
            "products": [
              "0-22ct-half-eternity-bezel-diamond-band",
              "bezel-set-marquise-shape-diamond-ring"
            ]
          }
        },
        "rich_text_GrzH6c": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Key Components",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Key Components of a Bezel Setting</h2><p>Let’s break it down:</p><ul><li>Rim (or Collar): This is the part that encircles the diamond. It can be thin and minimal or thicker for a bolder look. It’s shaped to fit the stone exactly, usually through careful polishing and precision.</li><li>Seat: This is where the diamond rests. It’s carved out of the metal so that the stone can sit in-line. The seat is usually made just deep enough to keep the diamond secure, without burying it too far below the rim.</li><li>Base / Gallery: Underneath the stone, you’ll find the base of the setting, this can be solid or open, depending on how much light the jeweller wants to let in. Some designs feature tiny cut-outs to add airiness or let more light reach the stone.</li></ul><p>Together, these parts work to hold the diamond gently but firmly, making sure it’s safe without stealing the spotlight</p>",
            "custom_id": "components",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_CQ3bf3": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Types",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Types of Bezel Settings</h2><p>Bezel settings aren’t one-size-fits-all. There’s a surprising amount of variety, even within this seemingly simple design. Here are a few types you might encounter:</p><h3>Full Bezel</h3><p>The entire perimeter of the diamond is encased in metal. This is the most secure version and provides excellent protection. It’s also the most classic and clean-looking.</p><h3>Half Bezel</h3><p>As the name suggests, only part of the stone is surrounded, usually the sides with the top and bottom left open. This lets in more light and creates a more contemporary look while still offering some level of protection.</p><h3>Flush Bezel</h3><p>The diamond sits flush against the band, as though gently pressed into place. This type is popular in men’s rings or minimalist designs making it incredibly durable.</p><h3>Split Bezel</h3><p>Some bezels incorporate design elements like milgrain (tiny metal beads), split bands, or mixed metals to add character. These don’t change the function, but they do shift the style.</p>",
            "custom_id": "types",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_XyXDjf": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Misconception",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Misconceptions about Bezel Setting</h2><p>One of the common misconceptions about Bezel Settings is that they dull a diamond’s brilliance. While it’s true that a bezel can limit how much light enters from the sides, modern design and clever engineering have minimized that issue.</p><p>In fact, the bezel can enhance certain diamond shapes. Ovals, marquises, and emerald cuts, stones with softer curves or longer proportions often look more defined in a bezel. The metal rim creates contrast and highlights the lines of the gem.</p>",
            "custom_id": "misconception",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_UiR3iy": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/The_Anatomy_of_a_Bezel_Setting_Components_Types_Durability_2nd_Image_Hq_2.jpg",
            "text": "<h2>Why Bezel = Built for Movement</h2><p>In sports, movement is constant, quick turns, fast reactions, high-impact motion. The same holds true for life. You move through your day, from workouts to meetings to celebrations, and your jewelry needs to keep up.</p><p>Prongs can catch. Bezel doesn’t.</p><ul><li>No sharp edges to snag on fabrics, gloves, or hair.</li><li>No weak points to loosen with impact or time.</li><li>No need to constantly remove your jewelry for workouts, travel, or daily activity.</li><li>Water-resistant and sweatproof by design: perfect for swimming, tennis, yoga, or any sport where your body stays in motion.</li></ul><p>Think of it like athletic gear for your diamonds: engineered, streamlined, built for performance without compromising elegance.</p>",
            "layout_direction": "row",
            "reverse_layout": true,
            "custom_id": "movement",
            "image_size_option": "medium",
            "show_products": true,
            "products": [
              "classic-bezel-round-diamond-eternity-ring",
              "7-01-ct-bezel-emerald-diamond-tennis-bracelet"
            ]
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_tU8WPR": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/The_Anatomy_of_a_Bezel_Setting_Components_Types_Durability_560_x_400_px_Inside_3rd_imageImage.png",
            "text": "<h2>The Durability Advantage</h2><p>Bezel settings don’t just survive daily wear, they’re made for it.</p><ul><li>Security: Diamonds are fully locked in place from every angle.</li><li>Longevity: Less maintenance compared to prongs (no tightening, no shifting).</li><li>Impact Resistance: The protective rim shields the diamond edge from accidental bumps or hits.</li></ul>",
            "layout_direction": "row",
            "reverse_layout": false,
            "custom_id": "durability",
            "image_size_option": "adaptive",
            "show_products": true,
            "products": [
              "aura-bezel-diamond-mens-band",
              "bezel-set-marquise-shape-diamond-ring"
            ]
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_x7hdVz": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/The_Anatomy_of_a_Bezel_Setting_Components_Types_Durability_560_x_400_px_Inside_4th_Image.png",
            "text": "<h2>The Lucira Approach: Bezel Reimagined for Modern Life</h2><p>At Lucira, we design every bezel piece through the lens of modern movement.<br/>We aren’t just creating jewelry. We’re engineering fine jewelry the way athletes approach performance gear, with precision, protection, and confidence in every motion.</p><p>Whether you're lifting, running, traveling, or building, your brilliance moves with you.</p>",
